def distinct_modulo(nums):
    modulo_nums = [num % 42 for num in nums]  # list comprehension
    return len(set(modulo_nums))

def main():
    nums = []
    for _ in range(10):
        nums.append(int(input()))
    print(distinct_modulo(nums))

def main():
    # Dictionary to store the modulo values
    mod = {}
    # Loop through 10 inputs
    for i in range(10):
        # Store the modulo of the input
        mod[i] = int(input()) % 42
    # Output the number of distinct modulo values
    print(len(set(mod.values())))

    main()
